The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Wednesday, June 02, 2004  Business Briefs																								 Mumbai, June 1: The Maharashtra Electricity Regulatory Commission today ruled in favour of Reliance Energy over the long drawn dispute between REL and Tata Power on sharing of the standby charges. MERC has directed Tata Power to refund Reliance Energy Rs 322 crore and pay Rs 58 crore towards unpaid standby charges to MSEB. TPC has been asked to share 77/79 per cent of the standby charges and REL to share 21/23 per cent.																								 New Delhi, June 1: Indian Airlines has increased the airfare by Rs 200 with immediate effect on all international sectors and domestic routes leading to international destinations.																								 New Delhi, June 1: The Metropolitan Magistrate today convicted both chairman and managing director of Montari Industries, in a case filed by Mudra Ispat, a unit of Ispat group, under the Negotiable Instruments Act. 																								 Mumbai, June 1: Bayer CropScience is planning to transfer its chemical and part of polymers business to Bayer Rubber Chemicals Pvt Ltd.																								 New Delhi, June 1: Jubilant Organosys has acquired 80 per cent equity in Belgiums Pharmaceutical Services Inc and PSI Supply NV for Rs 75 crore.
